IS  - 2
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - We consider a portfolio model with an infinite planning horizon. It is shown that the investment policy of maximizing the expected log each period is optimal when the utility function depends only on the tail of the sequence representing the capital at each period.
AB  - We consider a portfolio model with an infinite planning horizon. It is shown that the investment policy of maximizing the expected log each period is optimal when the utility function depends only on the tail of the sequence representing the capital at each period.
